  <p>
    This is almost my entire physical music collection. I still have more records, some CDs, and cassettes to add to Discogs. <em>Massive</em> shoutout to <a href="https://damianwalsh.co.uk/">Damian Walsh</a> who did all of the heavy lifting here. You need to read <a href="https://damianwalsh.co.uk/posts/creating-connections-with-music-and-technology/">his post</a> about why he created it. His collection has quite a few more features, it's built extremely well and is beautifully designed. This feels like theft because it is, really. But, I can't imagine it being setup any other way.</p>

  <p>I did make a few adjustments here and there to display records the way I wanted. Mostly to handle the duplicates. I'm a bit of a collector and like to have specific pressings of some albums.
  </p>
  <p>
    I learned a ton about Eleventy in the process. It's not 100% complete, and when I get the blog setup I will write more about it. In the meantime, poke around. 
  </p>
</section>

